 the recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i>. <br>- Once thoroughly chilled, these cheesecakes can be frozen for serving later.<br>- Instead of jars use small heat-resistant drinking glasses or coffee cups.","Add flavourings to the filling (e.g. zest from one lemon or lime, <b>½ tsp ground<b> cinnamon).<br>- For a nut-free version, omit nuts and use <b>60 g biscuits.<b><br>- For a lighter version, omit the crumb base.<br>- Instead of cooked berries, top with fresh seasonal fruit, caramel sauce or chocolate ganache."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","4h","6 jars"]}